<p>When Jeff Bezos began Amazon in 1994, he started out of a garage, selling books. Today, Amazon is a multi-national billion-dollar online retailer of more than 12 million products from manufacturers and second-hand markets. Sourced from global <em>and</em> local markets, Amazon can provide a nearly endless selection goods and products for customers anywhere. For more information on the Amazon company, see the <strong>About Us</strong> page on the <a href="https://www.aboutamazon.com/about-us" target="_blank"><strong>Amazon website</strong></a>.</p>

